svn path=/trunk/koffice/; revision=143443

Getting ready to implement Undo/Redo, i.e. off-loading most memory management
work to KShared/KSharedPtr.  Also ported some stuff to use QValueVector instead
of QPtrList.  The move is made for several reasons, we don't want somebody using
the auto-delete feature of QPtrList since the objects contained are KSharedPtr<T>,
an array makes more sense and I'm hoping the ISO C++ 98 will be widespread enough someday
to simply do QValueVector -> std::vector

svn path=/trunk/koffice/; revision=142251

First set of changes to move layers and channels to be krita paint devices.  This breaks a lot
and a lot of stuff.

Basically.

- Move tile management to it's own class.
- Make a tile class, this will allow for some nice per tile on/off features like masks.
- Make a layer keeps it's own tiles.  90% of the time, photoshop users don't use channels, they
use all channels combined, don't take the hit every time to recompose the tiles.
- Turn off a lot of stuff that hasn't been ported yet.
